HEADWORD: Sister-in-law
<hw>Sis"ter-in-law`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Sisters-in-law</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>The sister of one's
husband or wife; also, the wife of one's brother; sometimes, the wife of
one's husband's or wife's brother.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

